node.text:
Poor Ethel misses her sister. I really want to put her in with Woody but I’m so strict on quarantine. I just wonder if she could have anything she could pass to him. I doubt it. She’s displaying zero symptoms of being ill.

Until then, she’s taking comfort in Grandma Blanche’s favorite bed.

Thank you for all the messages of love and support. I’m always hesitant to share the bad parts of fostering because I never want to discourage anyone from fostering.  We take in the most critical cases to foster. Not all kittens are this complicated and need this much care. There are easy foster kitties out there that just need a safe place to stay temporarily until they are ready for adoption.

#fosterkitten #LucyAndEthelKitties

node.text:
You definitely don’t need an entire room to be able to foster kittens. A spare bathroom, a pet playpen or even an extra large dog kennel works great.

I also don’t give kittens access to things that I can’t easily disinfect or throw away (more expensive cat scratchers or cat condos) until I know they are healthy. I make sure that they don’t have anything they can spread (diarrhea, fungus, URI, etc.) before I give them access to these things.

Mama Sprinkle’s babies are 6-weeks old and as you can see they are full of playful energy! I’m so happy to bring Grandma Blanche’s quilt into their room. It brought her joy and it’s only fitting to have with these joyful babies.

Thank you to @parkandbench for this awesome boom box scratcher! It’s a big hit with the kitties and mama likes to hide out inside.

node.text:
Welcome new fosters!

Mama and her 3 precious babies born just a few hours ago! We don’t yet know if mama is friendly or not. We also don’t know if she is done delivering kittens. C5 trapper @seapurrtle trapped mama (thank you!) and on her way to be spayed, she started delivering.

Most rescue groups around Las Vegas are currently on intake hold (they’re all FULL) so I decided to take them in and foster them myself.

Thankfully this will be mama‘s last litter and all of these kittens will be spayed and neutered prior to adoption to STOP the cycle.

#spayandneuter #TNR #kittenseason

node.text:
Las Vegas or Southern California!

Both Chickadee and Portobella are looking for homes! Doesn’t have to be together, although that would be fun!

We are located in Las Vegas, but I’m traveling to Southern California next week and can deliver!

Chickadee is scheduled for her spay surgery on Thursday. She is a sweet, chunky little girl! She loves to play and she just has a really happy disposition. She does have an overbite that needs to be monitored in the future. Whoever adopts her, would need to commit to future veterinary care to make sure her adult teeth are not pushing into the roof of her mouth. She may need dental work in the future, but we are not sure.

Portobella has blossomed into a purring love bug. She’s a little nervous when you first approached her, but if I stick my finger out and let her sniff me she lets me scoop her up and the minute I hold her she melts and will purr non-stop!

Both girls would do good with friendly cats or gentle dogs, provided you do a slow, proper introduction of course.

If you are interested in adopting either one of these girls, please click on the link in my bio and complete an adoption inquiry form.

Please share!

#spayandneuter #adoptme #adoptus #availableforadoption #spayandneuter #fosterkitten #catsofinstagram #instakitten #losangeles #lasvegas #kittens #chickadeethekitty #fungusamonguskitties #adoptdontshop

Truffle and Shiitake have moved from the kennels to the big kid foster room!

Please don’t think you need to have a dedicated room for fosters. A pet playpen, spare bathroom or XL dog kennel works just fine.

READY FOR A FAMILY!

We’ve been working a lot with little Portobella. She loves to be held and cuddled. She really loves playing with toys. She is still skittish and will hiss when you approach her, but the minute you pick her up, she melts and starts to purr.

She needs a loving home that will continue to allow her to blossom. I think she would be good with another cat or on her own as long as someone is home with her to give her love and attention.

She is about 4-months-old and already spayed and vaccinated.

If you are in Las Vegas or willing to travel here to adopt, click on the link in my bio to complete an adoption inquiry form. She can also be transported to Southern California!

#3HotsandaCot #fosteringsaveslives #catsofinstagram #fungusamonguskitties #fosterkitten #adoptme #adoptdontshop

Check out Portobella!

We have had her separated from her siblings because she was the spiciest. We put her in a large playpen to gently push her out of her comfort zone. We’ve had her upstairs in the loft area so every time we walk by, she sees us and and took away anything that allowed her to hide away from us. 3 hots and a cot 😜

This is allowed her to get used to household noises. She hears the washer and dryer, vacuum and dogs barking. She’s been hissing at us anytime we go to pick her up so I pick her up with a blanket. In this video you will see my husband approaching her over and over again to get used to a hand coming towards her. It’s working! She’s coming out of her shell.

No more wrapping her in a burrito now, she has progressed to a tostada!

She still cannot have access to the entire house because I want to discourage hiding eventually, she will get there.

She also has no visible ringworm lesions like her brother does but has still been receiving regular antifungal baths as a precaution and all her bedding is washed frequently.

I’d say we’re pretty close to finding her a forever home! It’s going to need to be with someone who’s willing to continue to allow her to blossom, but she’s making excellent progress!
